cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a peer-to-peer network for community sensing, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel framework based on parallelized stochastic gradient descent for learning the low-rank structure of the sensor data, which falls under the scope of machine learning. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a decentralized framework for community sensing, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for community sensing, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a novel framework for approximating the value of sensor data in each subarea, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
